post_text:
At this time here are the attendance guidelines for home events at West Burlington this fall to help with social distancing. These may be subject to change with % positive rate and spectator behavior. Masks will be required when social distancing can't happen.
Spectators for JH events are asked to still sit/stand in these sections of up to 4 family members, however, reservations will not need to be made in advance because they don't go over capacity.
Admission is $5 for HS and $3 for JH events for everyone Kindergarten and older. Exact change or credit card must be used. Passes will also be accepted.
Concessions will be available with drinks $2, pizza $3, popcorn $1 and candy $1, so no outside food or drink is permitted. For indoor events we ask that concessions stay in the cafeteria. Exact change or credit card must be used.
All home events will be webcast linked on the district Facebook page and if away events are webcast that information will also be linked on our district Facebook. Rosters will not be printed and can be found here:
Thanks for your understanding and Go Falcons!

post_text:
CONGRATULATIONS WE ARE PROUD OF YOU!🏐💗🏐💗🏐💗🏐

An exciting night of volleyball tonight! We got the Win over 1A state ranked New London! It wasn't always pretty, but we rallied and wanted the win bad enough! The Seniors all stepped up and played their hearts out for Senior night and we had two sophomores break two game records!

Congrats to all of these girls for playing like a team tonight, and also to Sophomore Sydney Marlow for breaking Shayleigh Abbott's match high Kill record with 26 kills tonight! Also, congrats to Sophomore Kadence Johnson for breaking our own assistant coach, Kassidy Guihan's match high record with 46 digs!

Congrats to all of these girls for playing like a team tonight, and also to Sophomore Sydney Marlow for breaking Shayleigh Abbott's match high Kill record with 26 kills tonight! Also, congrats to Sophomore Kadence Johnson for breaking our own assistant coach, Kassidy Guihan's match high record with 46 digs!

June 18, 2018 at 3:50 PM ·

Your valuables are important us! On Thursday, June 14th, a member of our staff found a class ring from a 2018 graduate named Kelsy. The ring is being safely kept at the Burlington Y waiting for its owner. In order to claim the ring, you'll have to be able to describe it and provide photo identification matching the name on the ring.

post_text:
Falcons! It is Homecoming Week! Let's see your school spirit! (High School Students)

Dress Up Days:
Friday, September 1 - Heroes vs. Villains Day
Tuesday, September 5 - Sleeping Beauty Day
Wednesday, September 6 - Country vs. Country Club Day
Thursday, September 7 - Class Color Day
Seniors: Light Blue
Juniors: Red
Sophomores: Royal Blue
Freshmen: Purple
Friday, September 8 - Falcon Spirit Day

Homecoming week will end with the Homecoming Dance taking place on Saturday, September 9th at WBHS from 8:00-11:00 p.m. The cost is $5 each @ the door.
Have fun and make great memories!!!
